.Dd March 30, 2026
.Dt MORE 1
.Os Kayoko
.Sh NAME
.Nm more ,
.Nm moar
.Nd file perusal filter for crt viewing
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Ar file ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
utility is a filter to allow examination of continuous text one
screenful at a time.
.Pp
If invoked as
.Nm moar ,
the utility enables enhanced interactive features, including backward
scrolling and a terminal-clearing alternate screen buffer.
.Pp
When
.Nm
pauses, a footer is displayed at the bottom of the screen indicating
the current progress through the file as a percentage.
.Sh INTERACTIVE COMMANDS
The following commands are available while pausing:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Ic <Space>
Display the next screenful of text.
.It Ic <Enter>
Scroll forward one line.
.It Ic b , B
Scroll backward one screenful.
.Pq Er Moar mode only .
.It Ic /pattern
Search forward for the next occurrence of
.Ar pattern .
The footer will change to a
.Li /
prompt during input.
.It Ic v , V
Invoke the editor specified by the
.Ev EDITOR
environment variable (defaulting to
.Xr vi 1 )
at the current file.
.It Ic q , Q
Exit the
.Nm
utility.
.It Ic ^C
The interrupt signal is ignored to prevent accidental termination.
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width "EDITOR"
.It Ev EDITOR
Used by the
.Ic v
command to select an editor.
.It Ev COLUMNS
Used to determine the width of the screen.
.It Ev LINES
Used to determine the number of lines to display per screenful.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Ex -std
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr cat 1 ,
.Xr less 1 ,
.Xr vi 1
